Defendant in custody. 
State files an Amended Information charging the defendant with possess THC with intent to deliver, contrary to Section 961.41(1m)(h)2 of the Wisconsin Statutes, a Class H felony.   Motion granted.  Guilty plea to the amended charge.  Convicted.  Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years.  One (1) year initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.  Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  Defendant is given 95 days sentence credit.  Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Full-time employment or school or combination thereof;
2) Submit tn random urine screens and pay for same;
3) No contact with Jeremy Thompson;
4) Pay costs of action plus warrant fees;
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
